  "preFix": {
    "title": "Cauliflower cheese",
    "subtitle": "Proper cheese sauce, browned breadcrumb top",
    "excerpt": "A whole cauliflower blanketed in a thick, sharp cheddar sauce and baked until bubbling and golden on top. A Sunday side that many people eat as a main course.",
    "sourceNotes": "Mrs Beeton, Book of Household Management (1861), Project Gutenberg #10136. Cauliflower with white sauce and cheese.\n\nEliza Acton, Modern Cookery for Private Families (1845), Project Gutenberg. White sauce and baked vegetable dishes.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cauliflower cheese is a two-part recipe: a blanched cauliflower and a sharp cheddar sauce poured over and baked until golden. The sauce needs to be well-seasoned and thick enough to cling to the florets; a thin sauce produces a watery dish that separates in the oven.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "What you need",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
