        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Blanch the cauliflower",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oven to 200 degrees C fan. ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Blanch",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmpsohmu50000bcv4ecva6lrp"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " the cauliflower florets in a large pan of salted boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain thoroughly and leave to steam-dry for a few minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Make the cheese sauce",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Melt the butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add the flour and stir continuously for 2 minutes to make a roux. It should look like a smooth paste and smell faintly nutty.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Gradually whisk in the hot milk, a little at a time, whisking out any lumps before each addition. This is a ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "béchamel",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "termId": "cmp55wfv60001hgv4ozfcc4tj"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " base. Cook, stirring, until thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Remove from the heat. Stir in the 120 g of grated cheddar, the mustard, a generous grating of nutmeg, and salt to taste.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Assemble and bake",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Arrange the drained cauliflower in a pie dish or large gratin dish. Pour the cheese sauce over so it covers the florets completely.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Mix the breadcrumbs and remaining grated cheddar and scatter over the top. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until bubbling and deeply golden.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Add the milk very gradually, whisking constantly after each addition. If lumps form, pass the sauce through a sieve.",
                "cause": "The milk was added too quickly without whisking, or the roux was too hot.",
                "symptom": "The sauce is lumpy"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Steam-dry the blanched cauliflower for several minutes. The sauce should be thick enough to hold its shape when poured.",
                "cause": "The cauliflower was not drained well enough, or the sauce was too thin.",
                "symptom": "The dish is watery after baking"
              },
              {
                "fix": "A good layer of breadcrumbs and cheese browns well. If still pale after 30 minutes, turn the grill on for 3 minutes.",
                "cause": "Not enough breadcrumbs and cheese, or the oven was not hot enough.",
                "symptom": "The top is pale rather than golden"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use a mature cheddar. Season generously with salt; cheese sauce needs more salt than you expect.",
                "cause": "Underseasoned, or mild cheese was used.",
                "symptom": "The sauce tastes flat"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Smoked cheddar or a mix of cheddar and Gruyere gives a more complex flavour. Adding a tablespoon of wholegrain mustard in place of Dijon gives a coarser, more pungent sauce. Broccoli works in the same recipe, either alone or mixed with the cauliflower.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cauliflower cheese has been a British Sunday side since the mid-nineteenth century. Victorian cookery writer Mrs Beeton described cauliflower in white sauce as a standard accompaniment. The cheese version became dominant in post-war British cooking as cheddar became the nation's everyday cooking cheese. It is now the dish most likely to convert someone who claims not to like cauliflower.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    "servings": 4,
    "yieldDescription": null,
    "difficulty": "BEGINNER"
  },
